## Change Tracking Rules

After EVERY code change, update `DEVLOG.md` with:

- Timestamp
- File(s) modified
- What changed and why
- Sequence number

Format:

```
---
### [SEQ-NNN] YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm
**Files:** path/to/a.ts, path/to/b.tsx
**Action:** Short title of the change
**Details:** Concrete description of edits, behavior, or APIs touched
**Reason:** Why the change was made (ticket, bug, request, refactor)
---
```

Always increment the sequence number (`SEQ-001`, `SEQ-002`, …). Never skip an entry for a completed change batch. If multiple files are part of one logical change, use one entry listing all files.

Use the next sequence number after the latest `### [SEQ-...]` heading in `DEVLOG.md`.
